      302.67,
      193.61,
      316.67
    ],
    "text": "by the plaintiff.",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      96.38,
      335.79,
      519.33,
      349.79
    ],
    "text": "The general rule is that a deed of gift is absolute and irrevocable.",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      96.38,
      357.03,
      519.46,
      371.03
    ],
    "text": "However, under the Roman Dutch law, which is our common law, such",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      96.38,
      378.15,
      519.46,
      392.21
    ],
    "text": "a deed of gift can be revoked with the intervention of Court inter alia on",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle",
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
